{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH69ViSdVTFSEEp97G2L","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. The bug was in `src/pager.js`:\n\n```js\nconst nextStart = start + size - 1;   // off-by-one → next page repeats the last item\n```\n\nThe cursor contract in `src/cursor.js` states a cursor is the **exclusive upper bound** — the index of the first item of the *next* page. Since `items.slice(start, start + size)` consumes items `[start, start+size)`, the next page must begin at `start + size`. The `- 1` made it start one item early, causing each page's last item to reappear at the top of the following page.\n\nChanged it to `start + size`. `npm test` passes (2/2)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":316,"cache_read_input_tokens":23262,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":316},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98600a4f-46c4-420c-a018-d22248d069ee","uuid":"2d596088-eeeb-4e1d-8bea-d5dbb2fe92d7","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:23:33.526Z","request_id":"req_011CdH69UcDkWTbx1yA2SwAA"}
